                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5271.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-19T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1912—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Second paragraph of your October 17, 10 p.m. <hi rend="italic">Des. Moines</hi>
                    sailed 18th for Vera Cruz from Progreso; will arrive daylight October 20.</p>
                <p>Orders were given that after Americans and their interests have been cared for
                    the commander may give such assistance and protection as is possible to
                    foreigners and their interests and to noncombatants. You may so inform the
                    German Chargé d’Affaires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
